Description: Fragmnet of oval handle to moderate turn of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine light brown. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Name Theudoros. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0638.39.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (251)
